<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-06-06T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-06-06T16:00:00-05:00" n="343" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d343">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.1211/5: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Summerlin</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-06-06T17:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">June 6,
                                        1921—5 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>83. Inform Department immediately what definite action adequately
                            protecting the rights and interests of American citizens in Mexico is
                            being considered by Executive, Congress, and Supreme Court.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>